    try:
        do_something()
    except TopException as ex:
        if ex.status_code != conflict:
            log('failed)

This code will not raise any exception, which was catch by TopException, it will just log something in case there is no conflict, otherwise it will pass. In my case it's:


    try:
        do_something()
    except ChildConflictException as ex:
        log('failed)
    except TopException as ex:
        pass

The only thing different from the first example is the fact, that I'm doing log in wrong place, it should be as follows:

        except os_exc.ConflictException:
